### Describe the bug

In `rest-client-reactive-quickstart` if we go to the ExtensionResource and modify the @Blocking GET request to look like this

```
@GET
@Path("/id/{id}")
@Blocking
public RestResponse<?> id(String id) {
    try {
        return RestResponse.status(RestResponse.Status.OK, extensionsService.getById(id));
     } catch (Exception ex) {
        return RestResponse.status(RestResponse.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, ex);
    }
}
```

And we add smallrye-openapi to the pom.xml
```
<dependency>
  <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>
  <artifactId>quarkus-smallrye-openapi</artifactId>
</dependency>
```

Then on application start up with `./mvnw compile quarkus:dev` the following warning is logged

`WARN  [io.sma.ope.run.scanner] (build-33) SROAP04005: Could not find schema class in index: java.lang.Object`

### Expected behavior

No warning is logged



### Actual behavior

Logged warning `SROAP04005: Could not find schema class in index: java.lang.Object`


### How to Reproduce?

1. `rest-client-reactive-quickstart` 
2. Navigate to ExtensionResource and modify the @Blocking GET request to look like this

```
@GET
@Path("/id/{id}")
@Blocking
public RestResponse<?> id(String id) {
    try {
        return RestResponse.status(RestResponse.Status.OK, extensionsService.getById(id));
     } catch (Exception ex) {
        return RestResponse.status(RestResponse.Status.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, ex);
    }
}
```

3. And we add smallrye-openapi to the pom.xml
```
<dependency>
  <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>
  <artifactId>quarkus-smallrye-openapi</artifactId>
</dependency>
```

